数据预处理¶

In [2]:
feature_extractor = BeitFeatureExtractor.from_pretrained('microsoft/beit-base-patch16-224-pt22k-ft22k')
model = BeitForImageClassification.from_pretrained('microsoft/beit-base-patch16-224-pt22k-ft22k', num_labels = 14, ignore_mismatched_sizes=True)

Some weights of BeitForImageClassification were not initialized from the model checkpoint at microsoft/beit-base-patch16-224-pt22k-ft22k and are newly initialized because the shapes did not match:
- classifier.weight: found shape torch.Size([21841, 768]) in the checkpoint and torch.Size([14, 768]) in the model instantiated
- classifier.bias: found shape torch.Size([21841]) in the checkpoint and torch.Size([14]) in the model instantiated
You should probably TRAIN this model on a down-stream task to be able to use it for predictions and inference.
In [3]:
class MyDataset(torch.utils.data.Dataset):
    def __init__(self, images, labels):
        self.data = feature_extractor(images=images, return_tensors="pt")
        self.data['labels'] = torch.LongTensor(labels)
        self.labels = torch.LongTensor(labels)

    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.labels)

    def __getitem__(self, index):
        return {
            'pixel_values' : torch.FloatTensor(self.data['pixel_values'][index]), 
            'labels' : self.labels[index]
        }
In [4]:
category = ['Argentina',
            'Belgium',
            'Brazil',
            'Coach',
            'Croatia',
            'England',
            'France',
            'Germany',
            'Goalkeeper',
            'Japan',
            'Poland',
            'Portugal',
            'Spain',
            'Uruguay']

images, labels = [], []
for idx, label in enumerate(category):
    for path in os.listdir('./team/' + label):
        image = Image.open('./team/' + label + '/' + path)
        images.append(image.convert('RGB'))
        labels.append(idx)
        
train_dataset = MyDataset(images, labels)
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset, batch_size=16, shuffle=True)

模型训练¶

In [5]:
optimizer = AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=5e-5)
num_training_steps = len(train_loader)
lr_scheduler = get_scheduler(
    name="linear", optimizer=optimizer, num_warmup_steps=0, num_training_steps=num_training_steps
)
device = torch.device("cuda") if torch.cuda.is_available() else torch.device("cpu")
model.to(device)
progress_bar = tqdm(range(num_training_steps))

  0%|          | 0/20 [00:00<?, ?it/s]
In [6]:
model.train()
for epoch in range(1):
    for idx, batch in enumerate(train_loader):
        print("{}...".format(idx))
        outputs = model(**batch)
        loss = outputs.loss
        loss.backward()
        
        optimizer.step()
        lr_scheduler.step()
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        progress_bar.update(1)

模型预测¶

In [7]:
model.eval()
fig, axs = plt.subplots(5, 3, figsize=(16, 16))
plt.subplots_adjust(top=1.8)  # 
plt.subplots_adjust(bottom=0.2)  # 
for (idx, path) in enumerate(os.listdir('./test/')):
    image = Image.open('./test/' + path)
    inputs = feature_extractor(images=image.convert('RGB'), return_tensors="pt")
    outputs = model(**inputs)
    logits = outputs.logits
    predicted_class_idx = logits.argmax(-1).item()
    axs[idx // 3][idx % 3].imshow(image)
    axs[idx // 3][idx % 3].title.set_text(path[:-5] + '\nPredicted Team:' + category[predicted_class_idx])
    axs[idx // 3][idx % 3].axis('off')
